1048.7, 940.4]}, {"text": "carryovers (“NOLs”), approximately $12.3 million of capital losses, and approximately $24.9 million of tax", "bbox": [137.6, 944.6, 1039.3, 965.4]}, {"text": "credits (“credits”), which expire at various times through the year 2025. Pursuant to Section 382 of the Internal", "bbox": [137.6, 969.6, 1064.7, 990.5]}, {"text": "Revenue Code, the Company’s utilization of such NOLs and approximately $2.0 million of tax credits are subject", "bbox": [137.6, 994.6, 1087.1, 1015.5]}, {"text": "to an annual limitation. The Company believes it is more likely than not that a portion of the federal NOLs and", "bbox": [137.6, 1019.6, 1063.6, 1040.5]}, {"text": "credits will expire before being utilized. Therefore, in accordance with FAS No. 109, “Accounting for Income", "bbox": [137.6, 1044.6, 1057.4, 1065.5]}, {"text": "Taxes” (“SFAS No. 109”), the Company has established a valuation allowance on the portion of NOLs and", "bbox": [137.6, 1069.6, 1033.3, 1090.5]}, {"text": "credits that the Company expects to expire prior to utilization. The Company also believes it is more likely than", "bbox": [137.6, 1094.6, 1070.8, 1115.5]}, {"text": "not that a portion of the credits and capital losses not subject to Section 382 limitations will expire before being", "bbox": [137.6, 1119.7, 1068.6, 1140.5]}, {"text": "utilized. Therefore, in accordance with SFAS No. 109, the Company has established a valuation allowance", "bbox": [137.6, 1144.7, 1028.8, 1165.5]}, {"text": "against the portion of these credits and capital losses that are expected to expire prior to utilization.", "bbox": [137.6, 1169.7, 964.1, 1190.5]}, {"text": "At December 31, 2007, the Company has state income tax NOLs of approximately $460 million and state", "bbox": [179.2, 1217.5, 1061.3, 1238.3]}, {"text": "credits of approximately $7.1 million available to offset future state taxable income. The state NOLs and credits", "bbox": [137.6, 1242.5, 1073.6, 1263.3]}, {"text": "will expire at various times through the year 2027. The Company believes it is more likely than not that a portion", "bbox": [137.6, 1267.5, 1083.3, 1288.4]}, {"text": "of the state NOLs and credits will expire before being utilized. Therefore, in accordance with SFAS No. 109, the", "bbox": [137.6, 1292.5, 1078.8, 1313.4]}, {"text": "Company has established a valuation allowance on the portion of NOLs and credits that the Company expects to", "bbox": [137.6, 1317.5, 1077.2, 1338.4]}, {"text": "expire prior to utilization.", "bbox": [137.6, 1342.5, 352.0, 1363.4]}, {"text": "At December 31, 2007, the Company has foreign income tax NOLs of approximately $5.5 million and", "bbox": [179.2, 1390.4, 1034.7, 1411.2]}, {"text": "capital losses of approximately $8.5 million, which expire at various times through the year 2017. The Company", "bbox": [137.6, 1415.4, 1078.6, 1436.2]}, {"text": "F-29", "bbox": [593.1, 1465.8, 632.4, 1486.6]}, {"text": "Form 10-K", "bbox": [1179.8, 949.9, 1208.4, 1085.5]}]}